From 2b8f42834272384bf5a81c3f75681622338c6c9d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andrey Kasaurov <andrey.kasaurov@amd.com>
Date: Thu, 1 Jan 2099 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] composable_kernel: fix intrinsic type mismatches for amd-main
 LLVM

The amd-main branch of llvm-project changed the signatures of several
AMDGPU intrinsics:

- __builtin_amdgcn_raw_buffer_load_b64/b128 now return unsigned int
  vectors instead of signed int vectors.
- __builtin_amdgcn_raw_buffer_store_b64/b128 now expect unsigned int
  vectors instead of signed int vectors.
- __builtin_amdgcn_mfma_f32_*bf16* intrinsics now expect signed short
  vectors instead of unsigned short vectors.
- __builtin_amdgcn_wmma_*bf16* intrinsics (GFX11/GFX12) now expect
  signed short vectors instead of unsigned short vectors for bf16
  operands.

composable_kernel uses signed int vectors (int32x2_t, int32x4_t) for
buffer load/store and unsigned short vectors (bhalf2_t, bhalf4_t,
bhalf8_t, bhalf16_t) for BF16 MFMA/WMMA operations, causing
compilation errors with the updated compiler.

Fix by adding explicit bit_cast conversions between the CK types and
the types expected by the intrinsics. This is safe because the
underlying bit patterns are identical -- only the C++ type-level
signedness differs.
